.SH NAME
HTMLTextAreaElement.validationMessage \- HTMLTextAreaElement:
validationMessage property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]validationMessage\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]HTMLTextAreaElement\f[R] interface returns a string representing a
localized message that describes the validation constraints that the
\f[CR]<textarea>\f[R] control does not satisfy (if any).
This is the empty string if the control is not a candidate for
constraint validation (\f[CR]HTMLTextAreaElement.willValidate\f[R] is
\f[CR]false\f[R]), or it satisfies its constraints.
.PP
If the \f[CR]<textarea>\f[R] element is a candidate for constraint
validation (\f[CR]willValidate\f[R] is \f[CR]true\f[R]) and the
constraints are not met (the \f[CR]HTMLTextAreaElement.validity\f[R]
object\[cq]s \f[CR]valid\f[R] property is \f[CR]false\f[R]), the value
is the error message that would be shown to the user during validation.
.SH VALUE
A string.
.SH EXAMPLE
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] textarea = document.getElementById(\[dq]myTextArea\[dq]);
\f[B]const\f[R] errorMessage = textarea.validationMessage;
.EE
